<br>
3. rolls, armor is one kinda roll, epic is another.. are weapons a 3rd? <br>
<br>
4. when do you know to call the raid? after such amount of time, or until you get to things the raid cant kill?<br>
<br>
5. drops (pp and money items) well i would guess the pp would go to the leading person to replenish the funds from gems. what about the money items, do they get handed out to people who stick threw the whole raid and dont get a drop, or do they go to raid leader to replenish costs too?<br>
<br>
I'm curious and I am hoping a few people who have lead a fear before could help me with the answers. Thank you<br>
<br>
Carolsue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umukhtaribnasim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukhtar Ibn Asim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(4/2/02 10:26:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2157.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear ?'s</span><hr size=1> 1. Peridots and jaspers are needed for symbols and runes.  I usually try and bring 3 extra stacks of each when I am leading.  Hand out 2 of the 3 stacks, primarily to clerics since rune is really only needed on the break or during demi/epic mob fights.  Keep the last stack in case people run out.  Only uses I can think of for pearls would be to CoH in latecomers, but if the plane is broken its not really needed (unless doing a north wall break in which case wanderers might still be up).  Suppose clerics might cast death pact too... but honestly not many use that spell that I know of.<br>
<br>
3. groups depend on levels.  If you have mostly 55+ its probably possible to do 2 groups. 60, means 1 group possible.  For most open raids the average level will be 51 or 52 which means you will need a minimum of 3 groups for the normal mobs and more for demis/epics.<br>
<br>
Group balance wise, for the average open raid you want 3 enchanters, though 2 can work in a pinch if one is 55+.  2 clerics.  At least 2 druids and 2 shamans.  2 warriors.  A fairly high level (55+ best) FD puller, either a SK or a monk will do... alternatively I have seen a 60 ranger harmony pull quite well though I am not sure how a lower level ranger would do.  The key to remember here is that Fear has an incredible aggro radius, but this aggro radius decreases as player levels increase.  After these essentials, make about half the raid melee, and half the raid nukers / backup healers.<br>
<br>
Typically I see open raids operate with 5 groups.  6 groups is fine too.  After having done a 7 group raid I never will again because at that size people start having trouble getting at normal size mobs, lag increases exponentially, LD's increase, chatter increases to the point where people start missing raid leader instructions, etc.  Open raids are typically called when total numbers fall below 3 full groups.<br>
<br>
3. Yep, armor and epics are different as are weapons.  Asside from armor and epic items I seldom see people making loads of noise to get in on rolls in Fear.  Stuff that drops there just isn't that great.<br>
<br>
4. Set conditions for calling the raid... Maximum time limit, minimum numbers of people you will operate with, decide if the raid is going to end after achieving a specific objective.  Also recognize that sometimes things just aren't working out right.  It is possible to get a number of folks who just don't get raiding and who will through no fault of their own other than ignorance, and dare I say it, stupidity will cause repeated trains.  If you can't single them out and TL them out of Fear then its best to call the raid rather than spoil everyone's evening with repeated wipeouts.<br>
<br>
5.  Money, money items, and gems to the raid leader is typical if he or she provides peridots.  Fear is very very stingy in comparison to Hate with these, so typically the raid leader will not be able to break even in Fear.  In cases where you have a good night and do break even then you would probably roll away special gems (Blue diamonds, etc).  Don't be too generous though, or if you are a good raid leader, people's enthusiasm for you to do more raids will quickly bankrupt you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
