</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(4/2/02 3:21:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2157.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear ?'s</span><hr size=1> Mukhtar has pretty much covered it, but I do have a 'few' comments myself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
1) You need peridots, really, and nothing else. If people can get by with the jasper based symbol (Pinzarn), they can get by without symbol at all. You don't need pearls either, as you won't need to deathpact anyone nor CoH. If your puller demands a mage in his group to CoH when he screws up, get a new puller who actually knows how to pull fear.<br>
<br>
You can save quite a lot on gems if your raiders are good at agro control, as then only the main assist and the enchanters will require symbols for the regular fighting in the plane. Of course this changes for the demis and draco, but you can save several stacks of gems by clerics not symboling every trigger hapy nuker thats afraid he might get agro when he's making a bid to get exp off all the mobs. Yes, that would be the same nuker who's asking for mod rods and twitches, which he should not get either.<br>
<br>
2) Unless you've got a lot of experience breaking fear, you'll want to use at least two groups for this. 2 clerics, 2 chanters, an evacer in each group and the rest tanks and nukers. Bards are great as well, as the better ones can lock down 4 mobs permanently without ever needing mana. Something your enchanters cannot. Depending on the average level of the raid, you may need to add more groups to the break in order to kill fast enough to hold it.<br>
<br>
Once the plane is broken, ie. you've killed most of the roamers on the west wall and around the portal, you can reasonably get by with a single cleric if you need to. As long as this cleric is bound in Feerott. Of course, more clerics are better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Definitely don't ever go above 6 groups in a raid, as Mukhtar said. The zone can handle it, but most people's computers can't keep up with showing that many people at once, cause lag and LDs. Besides your clerics and enchanters, just fill up with melee and casters of any class you want, though you ought to fit a wizard in there to TL people out if you don't manage to clear temple.<br>
<br>
For pulling, honestly any class can do it at 57+. It is a simple matter of knowing the plane. Even when you have a ranger or druid pulling, they will rarely if ever use harmony - the agro range of most mobs in fear is greater than the range of harmony, even at lvl 60. If they're pulling well, its due to them knowing how to go about it. As such, a paladin, warrior or any other class can do it well, if they know the plane. Even a wizard can pull it of well, though i'd recommend having epic for that to avoid being too much of a manasponge <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  When pulling in fear, FD really is not needed at any point except the temple pull. And one can get around that, too.<br>
<br>
3) This is your choice, as raid leader. 100% your decision. Just make sure people signing up know about it beforehand. Generally though, armor, epics and weapons are all seperate rolls.<br>
<br>
4) For your standard open raid, when the majority of the raid has to leave *or* when you've achieved the goals you set out to reach, would be a prudent time to leave. I tend to dislike leaving anything alive there though (well, except for Cazic Thule whom i've yet to have a raid capable of challenging), but thats just me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
